{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016scoUcPM5KH77BcCREy8fE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Backend Test & Settlement Patterns Report\n\n### 1. TEST FILE LOCATIONS & PATTERNS\n\n**Test File Locations:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/` — Main test directory\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/` — Event queue tests\n\n**Available Test Files:**\n- `referral-routes.test.ts` — Referral route endpoints\n- `integration.test.ts` — Full lifecycle create → join → settle\n- `queue.test.ts` — Event queue unit tests\n- `queue-integration.test.ts` — Event queue worker integration\n- `profile.test.ts`, `auth.test.ts`, `endpoints.test.ts`, `leaderboard.test.ts`, `fairness.test.ts`, and others\n\n**Test Framework:**\n- **Framework:** Vitest 2.1.0\n- **Config file:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/vitest.config.ts`\n- **Key setting:** `fileParallelism: false` (tests run sequentially to avoid TRUNCATE races on shared Postgres database)\n- **Environment:** `node`\n\n**Test Structure Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// Standard structure used across all tests\nimport { describe, it, beforeAll, afterAll, beforeEach, expect } from \"vitest\";\nimport postgres from \"postgres\";\n\ndescribe(\"Test suite name\", () => {\n  let sql: ReturnType<typeof postgres>;\n  \n  beforeAll(async () => {\n    // Create Postgres connection (via DATABASE_URL or Unix socket)\n    sql = process.env.DATABASE_URL\n      ? postgres(process.env.DATABASE_URL)\n      : postgres({\n          host: \"/var/run/postgresql\",\n          user: \"vscode\",\n          database: \"rng_utopia_dev\",\n        });\n  });\n  \n  afterAll(async () => {\n    await sql.end();\n  });\n  \n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    // TRUNCATE tables to reset state between tests\n    await sql`TRUNCATE event_queue, referral_codes, ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n  });\n  \n  it(\"test name\", async () => {\n    // Test implementation\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Key Helpers:**\n- Database isolation: `TRUNCATE ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE` in `beforeEach`\n- JWT creation: `SignJWT` from `jose` package\n- Mock wallet creation: `Keypair.generate()` from `@solana/web3.js`\n- User ID derivation: `usr_${wallet.slice(0, 8).toLowerCase()}`\n\n---\n\n### 2. REFERRAL EVENT EMISSION DURING SETTLEMENT\n\n**Event Type Definition:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n} as const;\n```\n\n**Event Emission Pattern:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,  // Works with both sql and tx from sql.begin()\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Referral Earnings Recording During Settlement:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` lines 113-199:\n\n```typescript\nasync function recordReferralEarnings(\n  db: Db,\n  params: {\n    roundId: string;\n    gameType: string;\n    feeBps: number;\n    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n    players: Array<{ wallet: string; wagerLamports: number }>;\n  },\n): Promise<void> {\n  // Deduplicate players (Lord of RNGs can have multiple entries per player)\n  const playerWagers = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const p of players) {\n    playerWagers.set(p.wallet, (playerWagers.get(p.wallet) ?? 0) + p.wagerLamports);\n  }\n\n  for (const [wallet, wagerLamports] of playerWagers) {\n    try {\n      const refereeProfile = await db.getProfileByWallet(wallet);\n      if (!refereeProfile) continue;\n      const link = await db.getReferralLinkByRefereeUserId(refereeProfile.user_id);\n      if (!link) continue;\n\n      const referrerWallet = link.referrer_wallet;\n      const referrerRateBps = await db.getReferrerRate(\n        link.referrer_user_id,\n        referralDefaultRateBps,\n      );\n\n      const feeLamports = Math.floor((wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000);\n      const referrerEarnedLamports = Math.floor(\n        (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000,\n      );\n      const refereeRebateLamports = Math.floor((feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000);\n\n      // Insert into referral_earnings (UNIQUE constraint provides idempotency)\n      await db.insertReferralEarning({\n        referrerUserId: link.referrer_user_id,\n        refereeUserId: refereeProfile.user_id,\n        referrerWallet,\n        refereeWallet: wallet,\n        roundId,\n        gameType,\n        wagerLamports,\n        feeLamports,\n        referrerEarnedLamports,\n        referrerRateBps,\n        refereeRebateLamports,\n        refereeRebateRateBps: 1000, // fixed 10% for v1\n      });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // Errors logged but never bubble — referral recording must not fail settlement\n      logger.error(\"failed to record referral earning\", { roundId, wallet, error });\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Integration Test Pattern:**\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` lines 689+:\n- Sets up referral link: `db.insertReferralLink()`\n- Creates a match\n- Settles the match via `settleMatch()`\n- Verifies `referral_earnings` table is populated with correct amounts\n- Pattern: Referral earnings are recorded **within the same DB transaction** as the settlement, ensuring atomicity\n\n---\n\n### 3. LATEST MIGRATION NUMBER\n\n**Latest Migration:** `010_referral.sql` (dated Apr 2, 13:09)\n\n**Migration Files in Order:**\n1. `001_init.sql` — Core tables (rounds, operator_events)\n2. `002_operator_events.sql` — Operator audit log\n3. `003_auth.sql` — JWT auth (challenges, refresh_tokens)\n4. `004_closecall_rounds.sql` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds\n5. `005_closecall_candles.sql` — Cached minute-boundary BTC prices\n6. `006_player_profiles.sql` — Player identity\n7. `007_game_entries.sql` — Participation + stats + leaderboard\n8. `008_transactions.sql` — Real on-chain SOL movements\n9. `009_event_queue.sql` — Async event processing\n10. `010_referral.sql` — **Latest** Referral system (codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates)\n\n**Migration Runner:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`:\n- Reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` directory\n- Tracks applied versions in `_migrations` table (version INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- Each migration runs in `sql.begin()` transaction for atomicity\n- Idempotent: skips already-applied versions\n- CLI commands: `tsx src/migrate.ts` (apply) or `tsx src/migrate.ts status` (show status)\n\n---\n\n### 4. DB TRANSACTION PATTERNS\n\n**Database Client Module:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Transaction Abstraction:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // ... other methods ...\n  \n  // Transaction helper — wraps sql.begin()\n  transaction<T>(\n    fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>,\n  ): Promise<T>;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Using sql.begin() for Transactions:**\nPattern used throughout codebase:\n\n```typescript\n// Pattern 1: Direct SQL transaction\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  const result = await emitEvent(\n    tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n    EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n    payload,\n  );\n});\n\n// Pattern 2: DB wrapper transaction\nawait db.transaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // Operations within txDb are atomic\n  await txDb.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\");\n  await recordReferralEarnings(txDb, {...});\n  // Either all succeed or all rollback\n});\n\n// Pattern 3: Migration pattern\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  await tx.unsafe(content);  // Run migration SQL\n  await tx.unsafe(\n    \"INSERT INTO _migrations (version, name) VALUES ($1, $2)\",\n    [migration.version, migration.name],\n  );\n});\n```\n\n**Query Patterns:**\n```typescript\n// Typed queries with postgres library\nconst rows = await sql<{ id: string; event_type: string }[]>`\n  SELECT id, event_type FROM event_queue WHERE status = ${\"pending\"}\n`;\n\n// JSON insertion\nconst rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n  INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n  VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n  RETURNING id\n`;\n\n// UPSERT pattern (game entries at settlement)\nawait sql`\n  INSERT INTO game_entries (user_id, wallet, game, round_pda, match_id, amount_lamports, is_winner, payout_lamports, settled_at)\n  VALUES (${userId}, ${wallet}, ${game}, ${roundPda}, ${matchId}, ${amount}, ${isWinner}, ${payout}, ${now})\n  ON CONFLICT (wallet, round_pda) DO UPDATE SET\n    is_winner = EXCLUDED.is_winner,\n    payout_lamports = EXCLUDED.payout_lamports,\n    settled_at = EXCLUDED.settled_at\n`;\n\n// Isolation level — explicit transaction control\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // TRUNCATE for test isolation\n  await tx`TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`;\n  // Multiple operations stay atomic\n});\n```\n\n**Key Libraries:**\n- `postgres` (v3.4.0) — PostgreSQL client with typed queries\n- **No ORM** — Uses raw SQL with type safety via query parameter templates\n\n**Settlement Transaction Pattern (Real Example):**\nFrom `settle-tx.ts`, settlement wraps multiple operations:\n1. Fetch secret from DB\n2. Update round phase: `locked → settling`\n3. Log operator event\n4. Record referral earnings (idempotent via UNIQUE constraint)\n5. Update round phase: `settling → settled`\n6. All within single `db.transaction()` call ensuring atomicity\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Test Framework** | Vitest 2.1.0 with vitest.config.ts `fileParallelism: false` |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL 16 via `postgres` library (raw SQL, typed queries) |\n| **Test Isolation** | `TRUNCATE ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE` in `beforeEach` |\n| **Transaction Pattern** | `sql.begin(async (tx) => {...})` for atomicity |\n| **Referral Settlement** | `recordReferralEarnings()` called within settlement transaction, idempotent via UNIQUE(referee_user_id, round_id) |\n| **Event Emission** | `emitEvent(tx, EventType, payload)` — inserts to `event_queue` table atomically |\n| **Latest Migration** | 010_referral.sql (referral system: codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates) |\n| **DB Query Style** | Postgres template literals with typed generics: `` await sql<Type[]>`query` `` |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee923df0-ca95-4460-8036-5b0289591b86","uuid":"82fd4ff5-a49a-4b44-a6fe-046fb3489933","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:49:53.715Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the test patterns used in the backend. Find and read:\n1. Any existing test files related to settlement or event queue (search for test files in `backend/services/backend/src/` or `backend/services/backend/tests/`)\n2. The referral event emission as a pattern example (how referral events are emitted during settlement)\n3. The migration files to understand the numbering (what's the latest migration number)\n4. The DB client patterns (how transactions work, db.query patterns)\n\nSearch in /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/\n\nReport:\n- Test file locations and patterns (how tests are structured, what test framework, helpers used)\n- How the referral system emits events during settlement (exact code pattern)\n- Latest migration number\n- DB transaction patterns","agentId":"a5ba4a2394647ee9f","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report:\n\n## Backend Test & Settlement Patterns Report\n\n### 1. TEST FILE LOCATIONS & PATTERNS\n\n**Test File Locations:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/` — Main test directory\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/` — Event queue tests\n\n**Available Test Files:**\n- `referral-routes.test.ts` — Referral route endpoints\n- `integration.test.ts` — Full lifecycle create → join → settle\n- `queue.test.ts` — Event queue unit tests\n- `queue-integration.test.ts` — Event queue worker integration\n- `profile.test.ts`, `auth.test.ts`, `endpoints.test.ts`, `leaderboard.test.ts`, `fairness.test.ts`, and others\n\n**Test Framework:**\n- **Framework:** Vitest 2.1.0\n- **Config file:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/vitest.config.ts`\n- **Key setting:** `fileParallelism: false` (tests run sequentially to avoid TRUNCATE races on shared Postgres database)\n- **Environment:** `node`\n\n**Test Structure Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// Standard structure used across all tests\nimport { describe, it, beforeAll, afterAll, beforeEach, expect } from \"vitest\";\nimport postgres from \"postgres\";\n\ndescribe(\"Test suite name\", () => {\n  let sql: ReturnType<typeof postgres>;\n  \n  beforeAll(async () => {\n    // Create Postgres connection (via DATABASE_URL or Unix socket)\n    sql = process.env.DATABASE_URL\n      ? postgres(process.env.DATABASE_URL)\n      : postgres({\n          host: \"/var/run/postgresql\",\n          user: \"vscode\",\n          database: \"rng_utopia_dev\",\n        });\n  });\n  \n  afterAll(async () => {\n    await sql.end();\n  });\n  \n  beforeEach(async () => {\n    // TRUNCATE tables to reset state between tests\n    await sql`TRUNCATE event_queue, referral_codes, ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE`;\n  });\n  \n  it(\"test name\", async () => {\n    // Test implementation\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Key Helpers:**\n- Database isolation: `TRUNCATE ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE` in `beforeEach`\n- JWT creation: `SignJWT` from `jose` package\n- Mock wallet creation: `Keypair.generate()` from `@solana/web3.js`\n- User ID derivation: `usr_${wallet.slice(0, 8).toLowerCase()}`\n\n---\n\n### 2. REFERRAL EVENT EMISSION DURING SETTLEMENT\n\n**Event Type Definition:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n} as const;\n```\n\n**Event Emission Pattern:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,  // Works with both sql and tx from sql.begin()\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Referral Earnings Recording During Settlement:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` lines 113-199:\n\n```typescript\nasync function recordReferralEarnings(\n  db: Db,\n  params: {\n    roundId: string;\n    gameType: string;\n    feeBps: number;\n    referralDefaultRateBps: number;\n    players: Array<{ wallet: string; wagerLamports: number }>;\n  },\n): Promise<void> {\n  // Deduplicate players (Lord of RNGs can have multiple entries per player)\n  const playerWagers = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const p of players) {\n    playerWagers.set(p.wallet, (playerWagers.get(p.wallet) ?? 0) + p.wagerLamports);\n  }\n\n  for (const [wallet, wagerLamports] of playerWagers) {\n    try {\n      const refereeProfile = await db.getProfileByWallet(wallet);\n      if (!refereeProfile) continue;\n      const link = await db.getReferralLinkByRefereeUserId(refereeProfile.user_id);\n      if (!link) continue;\n\n      const referrerWallet = link.referrer_wallet;\n      const referrerRateBps = await db.getReferrerRate(\n        link.referrer_user_id,\n        referralDefaultRateBps,\n      );\n\n      const feeLamports = Math.floor((wagerLamports * feeBps) / 10_000);\n      const referrerEarnedLamports = Math.floor(\n        (feeLamports * referrerRateBps) / 10_000,\n      );\n      const refereeRebateLamports = Math.floor((feeLamports * 1000) / 10_000);\n\n      // Insert into referral_earnings (UNIQUE constraint provides idempotency)\n      await db.insertReferralEarning({\n        referrerUserId: link.referrer_user_id,\n        refereeUserId: refereeProfile.user_id,\n        referrerWallet,\n        refereeWallet: wallet,\n        roundId,\n        gameType,\n        wagerLamports,\n        feeLamports,\n        referrerEarnedLamports,\n        referrerRateBps,\n        refereeRebateLamports,\n        refereeRebateRateBps: 1000, // fixed 10% for v1\n      });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // Errors logged but never bubble — referral recording must not fail settlement\n      logger.error(\"failed to record referral earning\", { roundId, wallet, error });\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Integration Test Pattern:**\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` lines 689+:\n- Sets up referral link: `db.insertReferralLink()`\n- Creates a match\n- Settles the match via `settleMatch()`\n- Verifies `referral_earnings` table is populated with correct amounts\n- Pattern: Referral earnings are recorded **within the same DB transaction** as the settlement, ensuring atomicity\n\n---\n\n### 3. LATEST MIGRATION NUMBER\n\n**Latest Migration:** `010_referral.sql` (dated Apr 2, 13:09)\n\n**Migration Files in Order:**\n1. `001_init.sql` — Core tables (rounds, operator_events)\n2. `002_operator_events.sql` — Operator audit log\n3. `003_auth.sql` — JWT auth (challenges, refresh_tokens)\n4. `004_closecall_rounds.sql` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds\n5. `005_closecall_candles.sql` — Cached minute-boundary BTC prices\n6. `006_player_profiles.sql` — Player identity\n7. `007_game_entries.sql` — Participation + stats + leaderboard\n8. `008_transactions.sql` — Real on-chain SOL movements\n9. `009_event_queue.sql` — Async event processing\n10. `010_referral.sql` — **Latest** Referral system (codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates)\n\n**Migration Runner:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`:\n- Reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` directory\n- Tracks applied versions in `_migrations` table (version INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- Each migration runs in `sql.begin()` transaction for atomicity\n- Idempotent: skips already-applied versions\n- CLI commands: `tsx src/migrate.ts` (apply) or `tsx src/migrate.ts status` (show status)\n\n---\n\n### 4. DB TRANSACTION PATTERNS\n\n**Database Client Module:**\nLocated in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Transaction Abstraction:**\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // ... other methods ...\n  \n  // Transaction helper — wraps sql.begin()\n  transaction<T>(\n    fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>,\n  ): Promise<T>;\n  \n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**Using sql.begin() for Transactions:**\nPattern used throughout codebase:\n\n```typescript\n// Pattern 1: Direct SQL transaction\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  const result = await emitEvent(\n    tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n    EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n    payload,\n  );\n});\n\n// Pattern 2: DB wrapper transaction\nawait db.transaction(async (txDb) => {\n  // Operations within txDb are atomic\n  await txDb.updateRoundPhase(pda, \"settled\");\n  await recordReferralEarnings(txDb, {...});\n  // Either all succeed or all rollback\n});\n\n// Pattern 3: Migration pattern\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  await tx.unsafe(content);  // Run migration SQL\n  await tx.unsafe(\n    \"INSERT INTO _migrations (version, name) VALUES ($1, $2)\",\n    [migration.version, migration.name],\n  );\n});\n```\n\n**Query Patterns:**\n```typescript\n// Typed queries with postgres library\nconst rows = await sql<{ id: string; event_type: string }[]>`\n  SELECT id, event_type FROM event_queue WHERE status = ${\"pending\"}\n`;\n\n// JSON insertion\nconst rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n  INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n  VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n  RETURNING id\n`;\n\n// UPSERT pattern (game entries at settlement)\nawait sql`\n  INSERT INTO game_entries (user_id, wallet, game, round_pda, match_id, amount_lamports, is_winner, payout_lamports, settled_at)\n  VALUES (${userId}, ${wallet}, ${game}, ${roundPda}, ${matchId}, ${amount}, ${isWinner}, ${payout}, ${now})\n  ON CONFLICT (wallet, round_pda) DO UPDATE SET\n    is_winner = EXCLUDED.is_winner,\n    payout_lamports = EXCLUDED.payout_lamports,\n    settled_at = EXCLUDED.settled_at\n`;\n\n// Isolation level — explicit transaction control\nawait sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n  // TRUNCATE for test isolation\n  await tx`TRUNCATE event_queue RESTART IDENTITY`;\n  // Multiple operations stay atomic\n});\n```\n\n**Key Libraries:**\n- `postgres` (v3.4.0) — PostgreSQL client with typed queries\n- **No ORM** — Uses raw SQL with type safety via query parameter templates\n\n**Settlement Transaction Pattern (Real Example):**\nFrom `settle-tx.ts`, settlement wraps multiple operations:\n1. Fetch secret from DB\n2. Update round phase: `locked → settling`\n3. Log operator event\n4. Record referral earnings (idempotent via UNIQUE constraint)\n5. Update round phase: `settling → settled`\n6. All within single `db.transaction()` call ensuring atomicity\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Test Framework** | Vitest 2.1.0 with vitest.config.ts `fileParallelism: false` |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL 16 via `postgres` library (raw SQL, typed queries) |\n| **Test Isolation** | `TRUNCATE ... RESTART IDENTITY CASCADE` in `beforeEach` |\n| **Transaction Pattern** | `sql.begin(async (tx) => {...})` for atomicity |\n| **Referral Settlement** | `recordReferralEarnings()` called within settlement transaction, idempotent via UNIQUE(referee_user_id, round_id) |\n| **Event Emission** | `emitEvent(tx, EventType, payload)` — inserts to `event_queue` table atomically |\n| **Latest Migration** | 010_referral.sql (referral system: codes, links, earnings, claims, KOL rates) |\n| **DB Query Style** | Postgres template literals with typed generics: `` await sql<Type[]>`query` `` |"}],"totalDurationMs":171673,"totalTokens":74347,"totalToolUseCount":39,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":696,"cache_read_input_tokens":70301,"output_tokens":3344,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":696},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
